17) Linking of xlincks fails under Linux. I'm unable to link 
    with libXaw even though I have it installed and the linker
    is looking in the right directory! What can I do?

 -  First check if the library directory is correctly given in
    on link command and in the Make.config

 -  Second, by default we generated code and link with debugging
    option on (-g), which causes the Linux ld to link staticly
    and _not_ using the *.sa/*.so but instead the *.a library.
 
    If you do not care about the debugging information, just
    change the debug flag in the Make.config to exclude '-g',
    and try to link xlincks again. You might would like to 
    relink everything without '-g' to get dynamicly linked
    programs. 
   
 -  Contact us on by sending e-mail to lincks-bugs@ida.liu.se

