34) Do I have to have root privileges to run this stuff?

No.  Not unless you give root ownership of the database by setting OWNER
in Make.config to be root.  Other than that, we know of no reason why
anything would require any part of LINCKS being started as root.

We have, however, heard from SCO users that you do have to run the
"lincks" program as root in order to be able to log in.  We cannot test
this.

